cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.ET

The paper discusses safety and security issues related to RF-based wireless power transfer networks (WPTNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the need for dependable operation, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.ET (Embedded Systems).
